[SN]TITLE[SN]
Cyclone Pam: Royal Glamorgan doctor returns to Vanuatu to help

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A consultant from a Rhondda Cynon Taf hospital is to fly out to his homeland Vanuatu to help support doctors in the aftermath of Cyclone Pam.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Dr Les Ala from Royal Glamorgan Hospital in Llantrisant will fly out on Wednesday and is expected to stay for three weeks.
He is appealing for donations to help buy equipment and supplies.
Cyclone Pam tore through the South Pacific archipelago killing 17 people and displacing thousands.
